Why this C12 and not the cross-repo ones:
  PR #15 listed 3 candidates: cross-repo schema-types, cross-repo
  fk-predicate, cross-repo lance-graph PR. All three require coordinated
  vendor mirror edits + upstream PRs to AdaWorldAPI/ruff or
  AdaWorldAPI/lance-graph. This sprint stays in-repo: it widens the
  SurrealQL emission to typed `int` for the ironclad Rails `*_id`
  foreign-key naming convention. Pure projection-side work, no upstream
  coordination, and the heuristic is explicitly framed as a stopgap
  the proper `has_type` predicate from upstream will replace.

The inference rule (closed, ironclad):
  - field name ends with `_id` -> ColumnKind::Int
  - everything else            -> ColumnKind::Any
  No other heuristics. `*_at` -> datetime, `is_*` -> bool, etc. are
  TEMPTING but introduce ambiguity (e.g. `paid_at` is datetime in some
  schemas, plain string in others). Defer until we have real upstream
  type triples.

